  "page": {
    "documentTitle": "定錨效應 | Concept Reading Lab",
    "bodyClass": "knowledge-page knowledge-anchoring-effect",
    "heroHtml": "<div class=\"hero-inner\">\n  <div>\n    <p class=\"kicker\">Knowledge Study / bias / estimation / reference</p>\n    <h1>定錨效應</h1>\n    <p class=\"topic-subtitle\">Anchoring Effect</p>\n    <p class=\"thesis\">一個先出現的數字、說法或框架，常會像錨一樣拉住後續判斷，即使你知道它不完全可靠，也很難完全脫開。</p>\n    <div class=\"hero-prompt\">\n      <strong>Read For</strong>\n      <p>這一頁要把『只是先講個數字』和『後面整場討論都被它帶走』拆開，因為很多估時、談判與風險評估都在無意中被第一個參照點綁住。</p>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n  <aside class=\"hero-note\" aria-label=\"主題資訊\">\n    <dl class=\"lexical-meta lexical-meta--knowledge\" aria-label=\"主題摘要\">\n      <div>\n        <dt>主題類型</dt>\n        <dd>判斷偏誤 / 初始參照</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>核心問題</dt>\n        <dd>Initial reference points bias later estimates</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>主要判準</dt>\n        <dd>起始數值、調整幅度、資訊品質、估計獨立性</dd>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <dt>讀完產出</dt>\n        <dd>能在估計與討論裡看出第一個數字如何偷偷變成判斷重心</dd>\n      </div>\n    </dl>\n    <div class=\"knowledge-map\" aria-label=\"閱讀結構示意\">\n      <span>起點</span>\n      <span>拉力</span>\n      <span>偏移</span>\n    </div>\n  </aside>\n</div>",
    "mainHtml": "<aside class=\"compass\" aria-label=\"頁內導覽\">\n  <span>Reading Path</span>\n  <a href=\"#core\">讀法總覽</a>\n  <a href=\"#setup\">問題設定</a>\n  <a href=\"#lenses\">判準透鏡</a>\n  <a href=\"#psychology\">心理連結</a>\n  <a href=\"#applications\">現實映射</a>\n  <a href=\"#misreadings\">誤讀校正</a>\n  <a href=\"#questions\">延伸提問</a>\n  <a href=\"#sources\">來源</a>\n</aside>\n\n<article class=\"article\">\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"core\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Orientation</p>\n      <h2>第一個丟進場的數字，常比我們願意承認的更有牽引力</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">定錨效應不是說人完全不會調整，而是說我們往往調得不夠遠。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"core-card\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Core Tension</p>\n      <p>有參照點能加快討論，但若第一個參照本身任意或偏差很大，後續所有修正都可能在錯的重心附近打轉。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"principle-strip\" aria-label=\"本頁讀法\">\n      <div>\n        <span>01</span>\n        <strong>先警覺第一個數字的力量</strong>\n        <p>只要某個值先進入腦中，它就很難不影響後續估計。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>02</span>\n        <strong>再創造獨立估計</strong>\n        <p>讓不同人先各自估，通常比大家一起從同一個起點調整好。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div>\n        <span>03</span>\n        <strong>最後要求參照的來源</strong>\n        <p>數字不是因為先說就該信，而要問它從哪來。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"setup\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Setup</p>\n      <h2>從一場看似理性、其實被起始數字悄悄帶走的估計開始</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">定錨效應在談判、工期、預算與 KPI 目標設定裡都特別常見。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"definition-grid\">\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>最小劇情</strong>\n        <p>專案 kick-off 時有人先說『這應該兩週吧』，之後整場估時都在兩週附近小修，即使實際複雜度遠高於此。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"tile\">\n        <strong>真正難點</strong>\n        <p>真正危險的不是故意喊價，而是大家以為自己後來已經很理性地修正過。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"concept-flow\" aria-label=\"問題展開\">\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">先出現一個參照點</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">後續討論圍繞它調整</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-arrow\">→</div>\n      <div class=\"flow-step\">最終判斷仍留在它附近</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"paradox-frame\">\n      <strong>Key Point</strong>\n      <p>定錨效應最麻煩的地方，是它常發生在自認最理性的估計活動裡。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"lenses\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Lenses</p>\n      <h2>四個看起始參照的角度</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">不是所有起點都壞，但你得知道什麼時候它只是在幫你收斂，什麼時候它正在誤導。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"lens-grid\">\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>來源可信度</strong>\n        <p>這個錨來自資料、經驗，還是純口感？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>調整空間</strong>\n        <p>團隊真的願意大幅修正，還是只做表面微調？</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>任務陌生度</strong>\n        <p>越陌生的題目，人越容易過度依賴現成參照。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"lens-card\">\n        <strong>獨立性</strong>\n        <p>估計者是否有機會在聽到別人前先形成自己的判斷？</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"table-wrap\">\n      <table>\n        <thead>\n          <tr>\n            <th>情境</th>\n            <th>錨怎麼進場</th>\n            <th>後果</th>\n          </tr>\n        </thead>\n        <tbody>\n          <tr>\n            <td>估時</td>\n            <td>先說一個週數</td>\n            <td>整體排程在過低或過高區域附近打轉</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>談判</td>\n            <td>先開價</td>\n            <td>後續讓步都以該數字為軸心</td>\n          </tr>\n          <tr>\n            <td>產品目標</td>\n            <td>先訂一個 KPI</td>\n            <td>團隊後續會自然把想像綁到那個目標值上</td>\n          </tr>\n        </tbody>\n      </table>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"psychology\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Psychology</p>\n      <h2>為什麼第一個數字這麼有力</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">因為它提供了一個即時的心智支架，讓不確定世界突然有了可抓的起點。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>大腦討厭無基準</strong>\n        <p>一旦沒有參照，估計很難；有了參照就算不準也讓人感覺比較能開始。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>調整成本很高</strong>\n        <p>要完全擺脫第一個數字，常比我們想像中更費力。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>參照會偽裝成理性起點</strong>\n        <p>只要場面上像是在做估計，人就容易忽略它其實只是隨手拋出的錨。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <p class=\"micro-note\">定錨效應不是說人沒在思考，而是說思考很少從完全空白開始。</p>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"applications\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Applications</p>\n      <h2>把去錨技巧帶回估時、規格與談判</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">對工程與產品團隊來說，定錨效應特別常把早期隨口說的數字變成後續所有承諾的中心。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"example-grid\">\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>Sprint 估時</strong>\n        <p>若先報一個樂觀數字，整隊很容易一起在樂觀軸上修，最後再用加班補。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>需求規模</strong>\n        <p>一開始若把 feature 說得太小，之後風險訊號常會被壓成『再微調一下就好』。</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"example\">\n        <strong>供應商討論</strong>\n        <p>先開出的成本與交期會深深影響後面談判空間。</p>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"bullet-list\">\n      <li>重要估計前，先做獨立估值再一起對齊，能顯著降低第一個聲音的控制力。</li>\n      <li>若不得不從一個數字開始，至少把它標明是假設、範圍或暫估，而不是事實。</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"misreadings\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Misreadings</p>\n      <h2>三個常見誤讀</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">定錨效應不是說所有參照都該丟掉，而是提醒你參照會塑形。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"collocation-list\" aria-label=\"常見誤讀\">\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只要知道這偏誤就不會被影響</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>通常還是會，只是比較有機會設計防呆。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>那就完全不要先給數字</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>有時需要起點，重點是讓起點可質疑、可獨立修正。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"collocation-card\">\n        <div>\n          <strong>只有談判才有錨</strong>\n          <span class=\"register-tag\">校正</span>\n        </div>\n        <p>工程估時、風險評分與 KPI 設定同樣常被錨住。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"questions\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Questions</p>\n      <h2>我現在的估計，是來自分析，還是來自第一個丟進場的值</h2>\n      </div>\n    <div class=\"prompt-grid\">\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>如果沒聽過第一個數字，我自己會估多少</strong>\n        <p>這能幫你檢查錨的實際拉力。</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"prompt-card\">\n        <strong>這個起始參照是資料、類比還是純口感</strong>\n        <p>來源不同，應該享有的信任權重也不同。</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"template-note\">\n      <strong>延伸路線</strong>\n      <p>延伸閱讀可接 estimation, negotiation 與 planning fallacy。</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\" id=\"sources\">\n    <div class=\"section-heading\">\n      <p class=\"section-label\">Sources</p>\n      <h2>來源與整理方式</h2>\n      <p class=\"section-lede\">這一頁以 anchoring effect 為主，再把它帶回估時、談判與目標設定的場景。</p>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"source-grid\">\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>主概念</strong>\n        <p>Anchoring effect 條目整理了初始參照點如何影響後續判斷。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anchoring_effect\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Anchoring Effect</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>學術來源</strong>\n        <p>Tversky 與 Kahneman 的經典研究是理解定錨效應的重要起點。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anchoring_effect#History\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Tversky and Kahneman</a>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"source-card\">\n        <strong>相鄰場景</strong>\n        <p>Negotiation 條目可作為對照，看起始開價如何塑造後續協商。</p>\n        <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Negotiation\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer\">Negotiation</a>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"chapter\">\n    <div class=\"reference-box\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"section-label\">Reference</p>\n        <h2>下一步</h2>\n        <p>讀完後可以回頭看最近一次估時，檢查第一個說出口的週數後來到底拉住了多少討論。</p>\n      </div>\n      <a class=\"reference-link\" href=\"../knowledge-topic-template.html\">打開模板</a>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</article>"
  }
